text: Many students, when preparing for an university exam, try to think of the question "What would I put on the test if I was the professor?", but you can easily fool yourself that way. The correct question is "What would I put on the test if I was a retärded gibbon tasked with it?"

Reading an anecdote by St. Paisios about a demonically possessed man who was brought to his hut, very ill, it turned out he was wearing a "talisman" gifted to him by some meme sorcerer that brought the trouble.

He was told to throw it into the sea as to rid himself of the demon, but in the boat he froze up and was unable to get up on his feet or take the talisman off - entire situation really reminded me of the LoTR final scene at the volcano with the one ring, exact same "behavior"

Thankfully, he had friends with strong arms who had accompanied him, they managed to pry it off him by force (even though he fought) and threw it into the sea, soon afterwards he felt better, his health recovered, and so did his spiritual state. It's good to have strong friends.
